The paper discusses the simulation of channel sensing, coordination, and allocation in VANETs, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI) and specifically, the sub-category of wireless and mobile networking (cs.NI.WM). Additionally, the focus on safety and infrastructure suggests a potential fit for the sub-category of cyber-physical systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of algorithms and techniques for coordination and optimization, which could fall under the sub-categories of information theory (cs.IT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses simulation results, which could suggest a fit for the sub-category of modeling and simulation (cs.MS).
